eneral entertainment format. Paxson Communications purchased the station in 1998, changing its [[call signs in North America|call sign]] to '''KSPX'''. The station became a charter owned-and-operated station of its new Pax TV network (later i: Independent Television and now Ion Television) on August 31, 1998.\n\n==Digital television==\n\n{{ION DTV|29}}<ref>[http://www.rabbitears.info/market.php?request=station_search&callsign=KSPX#station RabbitEars TV Query for KSPX]</ref>\n\nIn 2014, KSPX began simulcasting [[Telemundo]] affiliate [[KCSO-LD]] on digital subchannel 33.2.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! [[Digital subchannel#United States|Channel]]\n! [[Display resolution|Video]]\n! [[Aspect ratio (image)|Aspect]]\n! [[Program and System Information Protocol#What PSIP does|PSIP Short Name]]\n! Programming\n|-\n| | 33.2 || [[480i]] || [[16:9]] || TLMD || [[KCSO-LD]] / Telemundo\n|}\n\n===Analog-to-digital conversion===\nKSPX shut down its analog signal, over [[Ultra high frequency|UHF]] channel 29, on June 12, 2009, as part of the [[Digital television transition in the United States|federally mandated transition from analog to digital television]].<ref name=\"Analog to Digital\">[http://hraunfoss.fcc.gov/edocs_public/attachmatch/DA-06-1082A2.pdf List of Digital Full-Power Stations] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130829004251/http://hraunfoss.fcc.gov/edocs_public/attachmatch/DA-06-1082A2.pdf |date=2013-08-29 }}</ref> The station's digital signal remained on its pre-transition UHF channel 48, using [[Program and System Information Protocol|PSIP]] to display KSPX-TV's [[virtual channel]] as 29 on digital television receivers.\n\n===Reduced power operation===\nOn August 30, 2019, the station temporarily reduced power, per [[special temporary authority]] (STA), from 1,000 [[kilowatt|kW]] to 4.3 kW to accommodate relocation of its transmitter site.  \n\nPower was increased to 48 kW on November 16, 2019. The station will remain at this power level until the spring of 2020. \n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|https://iontelevision.com/}}\n*{{TVQ|KSPX}}\n*{{BIA|KSPX|TV|TV}}\n\n{{ION California}}\n{{Sacramento TV}}\n{{ION}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kspx-Tv}}\n[[Category:Ion Television affiliates]]\n[[Category:Telemundo subchannel-only network affiliates]]\n[[Category:Television channels and stations established in 1990]]\n[[Category:1990 establishments in California]]\n[[Category:Television stations in Sacramento, California|SPX-TV]]\n", "name_user": "Armando619", "label": "safe", "comment": "May 1st", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/KSPX-TV"}
